FILED SENATE
May 5, 2025
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
S.J.R. 764
SESSION 2025
PRINCIPAL CLERK
S D
SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION DRSJR15325-LG-171
Sponsors: Senator Rabon (Primary Sponsor).
Referred
to:
1 A JOINT RESOLUTION PROVIDING FOR THE CONFIRMATION OF CHRISTOPHER J.
2 AYERS AS EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR OF THE PUBLIC STAFF OF THE NORTH
3 CAROLINA UTILITIES COMMISSION.
4 Whereas, under the provisions of G.S. 62-15, the appointment made by the Governor
5 of the Executive Director of the Public Staff of the North Carolina Utilities Commission is subject
6 to confirmation by the General Assembly by joint resolution; and
7 Whereas, the current term of Christopher J. Ayers expires on June 30, 2025, and the
8 Governor wishes to appoint him to another term; and
9 Whereas, the Governor has submitted to the presiding officers of the House of
10 Representatives and the Senate the name of his appointee, Christopher J. Ayers of Wake County,
11 to serve as Executive Director of the Public Staff of the North Carolina Utilities Commission for
12 a term to begin July 1, 2025, and expire June 30, 2031; Now, therefore,
13 Be it resolved by the Senate, the House of Representatives concurring:
14 SECTION 1. The appointment of Christopher J. Ayers as Executive Director of the
15 Public Staff of the North Carolina Utilities Commission for a term to begin July 1, 2025, and
16 expire June 30, 2031, is confirmed.
17 SECTION 2. This resolution is effective upon ratification.
*DRSJR15325-LG-171*

